  "correctAnswer": "31",
  "section": "Math",
  "steps": [
    {
      "title": "Set up",
      "content": "Translate the two given relationships into equations. &ldquo;44% of $h$ equals 62% of $j$&rdquo; gives $0.44h = 0.62j$, so $h = \\dfrac{62}{44}j$. &ldquo;$j$ is 22% of $k$&rdquo; gives $j = 0.22k$."
    },
    {
      "title": "Solve",
      "content": "Substitute $j = 0.22k$ into the expression for $h$: $$h = \\frac{62}{44} \\cdot 0.22k = \\frac{62 \\times 0.22}{44}k = \\frac{13.64}{44}k = 0.31k$$"
    },
    {
      "title": "Answer",
      "content": "$h$ is 31% of $k$, so <strong>31</strong> is correct."
    }
  ]
}
